-- Gold Reef, Italtile RMB Holdings, Sappi May Move in Johannesburg Trading
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2011-02-09T06:04:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-08/gold-reef-rmb-holdings-sappi-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined for
a second day, falling 11.37, or less than 0.1 percent, to
32,788.86 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    Gold Reef Resorts Ltd . (GDF SJ): The gaming and casino
company today presents legal arguments in favor of its merger
with Tsogo Sun Holdings at the Competition Tribunal. Gold Reef
slipped 1.29 rand, or 7.2 percent, to 16.65 rand.    Italtile Ltd . (ITE SJ): The ceramic-tile retailer said
that wreckage assumed to be the group’s company airplane was
found in the Robberg area near Plettenberg Bay on South Africa’s
south coast. Two crew and seven passengers were on board the
flight and their names won’t be released until their relatives
have been notified, the company said in a statement today. The
shares fell 5 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 4.20 rand.    RMB Holdings Ltd . (RMH SJ): The South African investment
company today issues 72.4 million shares to Royal Bafokeng
Holdings Ltd. as part of the latter’s 2.5 billion-rand ($349
million) acquisition of 5 percent in the listed financial
services company. RMB fell 39 cents, or 1 percent, to 37.16
rand.  Sappi Ltd. (SAP SJ): The world’s largest producer of glossy
magazine paper releases earnings for the first quarter through
December. Sappi climbed 15 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 38.51 rand.    Sekunjalo Investments Ltd . (SKJ SJ): The investment group
holds a shareholders’ annual meeting. The shares were unchanged
at 43 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) slipped less than 0.1 percent
to $27.29. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 3.1 percent to
$46.37. BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) advanced 0.6 percent to
$82.38. DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) added 2.4 percent to $4.75. Gold
Fields Ltd. (GFI US) increased 2 percent to $16.53. Harmony Gold
Mining Co. (HMY US) gained 1.6 percent to $11.24. Impala
Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US) gained 0.5 percent to $29.26.  Sappi
Ltd . (SPP US) climbed 2.6 percent to $5.49. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US)
added 0.3 percent to $51.80.  To contact the reporter on this story:
